1
00:00:39,070 --> 00:00:40,540
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

2
00:00:40,540 --> 00:00:41,970
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

3
00:00:44,940 --> 00:00:49,550
Momo promised she'd raise my baby well.

4
00:00:50,750 --> 00:00:52,850
We were as close as sisters.

5
00:00:55,860 --> 00:00:56,860
It's Mommy.

6
00:00:57,620 --> 00:01:00,830
Thank you for taking
such good care of the baby.

7
00:01:02,230 --> 00:01:03,230
Thank you so much.

8
00:01:03,800 --> 00:01:06,230
You poor thing.
You kept saying you felt dizzy.

9
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:08,700
How could this happen?

10
00:01:12,240 --> 00:01:13,240
The poor thing.

11
00:01:14,440 --> 00:01:16,480
At least he got to see
his mother's face...

12
00:01:17,840 --> 00:01:19,380
Don't worry.

13
00:01:24,320 --> 00:01:26,320
(Ju Shin)

14
00:01:27,950 --> 00:01:30,120
- Hello?
- Ba Ra...

15
00:01:30,520 --> 00:01:31,760
passed away at dawn.

16
00:01:34,260 --> 00:01:35,830
There won't be a funeral
before the burial.

17
00:01:53,750 --> 00:01:56,320
Is her granddaughter
really moving in next week?

18
00:01:56,520 --> 00:01:58,580
Yes. I spoke with her on the phone.

19
00:02:03,720 --> 00:02:05,390
I think I'm going to miss him.

20
00:02:06,060 --> 00:02:07,760
You should come and visit sometime.

21
00:02:07,830 --> 00:02:09,400
I'll text you the address.

22
00:02:10,160 --> 00:02:12,100
- Would that be okay?
- Of course.

23
00:02:14,330 --> 00:02:16,800
Thank you. I know she was grateful too.

24
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:17,900
It was nothing.

25
00:02:17,970 --> 00:02:19,940
Ba Ra asked me to.

26
00:02:20,110 --> 00:02:22,610
- I've been paid more than enough.
- Please, I insist.

27
00:02:25,650 --> 00:02:26,650
Goodness.

28
00:02:26,980 --> 00:02:29,250
You should go back in.
The grandmother is all by herself.

29
00:02:29,720 --> 00:02:30,720
Right.

30
00:02:42,030 --> 00:02:46,100
She's not just a pretty face,
but an angel.

31
00:03:07,750 --> 00:03:08,750
Ba Ra.

32
00:03:11,190 --> 00:03:12,530
How could you leave me...

33
00:03:15,730 --> 00:03:16,860
and just go like that?

34
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:21,270
How could you?

35
00:03:46,260 --> 00:03:48,190
That looked like Geum Ba Ra, the reporter.

36
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:51,700
Well, I can just check.

37
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:55,970
(Reporter Geum Ba Ra)

38
00:03:58,040 --> 00:04:00,810
The number you have dialed
is not in service.

39
00:04:01,140 --> 00:04:03,580
Please check the number and dial again.

40
00:04:06,050 --> 00:04:08,780
The number you have dialed
is not in service.

41
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:12,390
- Please check the number and dial again.
- I'm heading out.

42
00:04:12,990 --> 00:04:13,990
Okay.

43
00:04:18,320 --> 00:04:20,590
Was she in a car accident or something?

44
00:04:38,140 --> 00:04:41,550
Shouldn't the baby see his mother off?

45
00:04:42,980 --> 00:04:46,720
Be sure to burp him
and lay him down gently on his side.

46
00:04:48,220 --> 00:04:50,590
He sometimes spits up, even after burping.

47
00:04:51,060 --> 00:04:52,060
Got it.

48
00:05:19,390 --> 00:05:20,790
(Momo)

49
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:26,760
(Momo)

50
00:05:30,630 --> 00:05:33,370
- Yes...
- The press will be there,

51
00:05:33,830 --> 00:05:35,670
so I think we should go together.

52
00:05:37,900 --> 00:05:39,170
I'm downstairs.

53
00:05:58,560 --> 00:05:59,590
Seatbelt.

54
00:07:39,460 --> 00:07:40,990
She was in the prime of her life.

55
00:08:32,140 --> 00:08:33,150
What's wrong?

56
00:10:58,590 --> 00:11:02,290
Book us a table at the Ria Hotel buffet.
For just us two.

57
00:11:02,360 --> 00:11:05,060
No. You know what will happen
if you overeat.

58
00:11:05,130 --> 00:11:07,400
Don't worry.
I will just eat in moderation.

59
00:11:07,670 --> 00:11:09,740
You think you can restrain yourself
in front of a feast?

60
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:11,170
I can if I have to.

61
00:11:12,270 --> 00:11:13,570
I can do anything...

62
00:11:14,810 --> 00:11:16,140
for my health.

63
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:20,010
We cleanse ourselves
of worldly dust and attachments.

64
00:11:20,250 --> 00:11:24,450
<i>We pray to the sky and the earth.</i>

65
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:30,260
<i>From the Muryangsa Temple</i>

66
00:11:31,060 --> 00:11:33,730
<i>Here in this world of suffering</i>

67
00:11:33,790 --> 00:11:37,360
<i>In Seodaemun District, Seoul, South Korea,</i>

68
00:11:37,630 --> 00:11:42,400
<i>In this pure sanctuary of Suwol</i>

69
00:11:42,900 --> 00:11:48,210
<i>At the request of</i>
<i>the humble devotee Ha Jae In</i>

70
00:11:48,470 --> 00:11:51,540
<i>We pray for the spirit</i>
<i>of the dearly departed Geum Ba Ra</i>

71
00:11:51,540 --> 00:11:53,280
<i>For the spirit of the dearly departed</i>
<i>Geum Ba Ra</i>

72
00:11:53,450 --> 00:11:57,220
<i>For the spirit of the dearly departed</i>
<i>Geum Ba Ra</i>

73
00:11:57,420 --> 00:11:58,780
<i>May she attain rebirth in paradise...</i>

74
00:12:11,730 --> 00:12:12,730
Let go...

75
00:12:13,730 --> 00:12:15,330
of all earthly attachments...

76
00:12:16,070 --> 00:12:17,140
and depart in peace.

77
00:12:39,060 --> 00:12:40,060
Thank you.

78
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:51,270
Drive safe.
I'll treat you to a meal sometime soon.

79
00:12:51,770 --> 00:12:52,770
Sure.

80
00:13:01,310 --> 00:13:02,980
She's really changed, that Momo.

81
00:13:07,820 --> 00:13:10,490
Such a waste of a pretty face
and a sharp mind.

82
00:13:10,790 --> 00:13:12,830
She must have studied so incredibly hard.

83
00:13:13,260 --> 00:13:15,130
And she never even had
one proper tutoring session.

84
00:13:15,260 --> 00:13:16,660
If she had married me,

85
00:13:20,430 --> 00:13:21,730
she wouldn't have died.

86
00:13:22,030 --> 00:13:24,700
Life and death are up to fate.
Her time was just up.

87
00:13:44,820 --> 00:13:45,820
Goodness.

88
00:13:47,890 --> 00:13:49,530
Did my little one burp?

89
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:52,130
You're so adorable.

90
00:13:58,900 --> 00:14:00,310
Your Daddy...

91
00:14:02,440 --> 00:14:04,040
cried so much today.

92
00:14:13,590 --> 00:14:14,690
Thank you.

93
00:14:15,920 --> 00:14:17,360
I hope you find peace...

94
00:14:18,690 --> 00:14:19,930
wherever you are.

95
00:15:15,210 --> 00:15:16,950
I'd like to pour you a drink.

96
00:15:37,600 --> 00:15:38,640
You've been through so much.

97
00:15:38,770 --> 00:15:39,940
You're the one who has.

98
00:15:40,910 --> 00:15:41,940
Thank you so much.

99
00:15:47,910 --> 00:15:49,050
Just take a sip.

100
00:16:01,560 --> 00:16:03,100
When are you going to tell Yong Joong?

101
00:16:05,860 --> 00:16:07,830
- You're not going to tell him?
- No.

102
00:16:07,900 --> 00:16:08,900
Why?

103
00:16:09,870 --> 00:16:11,940
They already decided
to go their separate ways.

104
00:16:12,240 --> 00:16:13,710
Then why did you ask me for the surgery?

105
00:16:14,440 --> 00:16:15,440
Just because.

106
00:16:17,640 --> 00:16:20,110
I'm a better fit for Momo than Jin Ju is.

107
00:16:23,580 --> 00:16:24,680
That's the only reason?

108
00:16:29,020 --> 00:16:30,660
Yong Joong is having such a hard time.

109
00:16:33,830 --> 00:16:34,860
Are you punishing him?

110
00:16:35,590 --> 00:16:36,860
I'll explain everything to him.

111
00:16:37,130 --> 00:16:38,260
It's not the right thing to do.

112
00:16:38,330 --> 00:16:39,730
We're way past doing the right thing.

113
00:16:40,830 --> 00:16:42,270
He and Momo just had a falling out.

114
00:16:42,270 --> 00:16:44,640
Saying it's me would just confuse him.

115
00:16:45,670 --> 00:16:47,770
He'd have to force his feelings
all over again.

116
00:16:51,240 --> 00:16:52,240
It's up to you.

117
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:55,210
I feel bad for Jin Ju.

118
00:17:08,530 --> 00:17:11,600
- Isn't there some way I can repay her?
- Of course there is.

119
00:17:13,530 --> 00:17:14,730
You'll be a fine replacement.

120
00:17:17,740 --> 00:17:18,800
I'm just kidding.

121
00:17:20,210 --> 00:17:21,670
I had a baby.

122
00:17:23,740 --> 00:17:24,740
A son.

123
00:17:38,860 --> 00:17:39,990
Did they move?

124
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:49,500
Hello.

125
00:17:53,310 --> 00:17:55,510
- Who is that?
- Excuse me?

126
00:17:55,740 --> 00:17:57,010
It's...

127
00:17:57,780 --> 00:17:59,180
Ba Ra's baby.

128
00:18:00,110 --> 00:18:01,310
What brings you here?

129
00:18:01,780 --> 00:18:04,750
- Excuse me?
- Security didn't alert me.

130
00:18:05,480 --> 00:18:06,790
How did you get in here?

131
00:18:14,660 --> 00:18:16,290
Wait, is that my key?

132
00:18:17,230 --> 00:18:19,030
You don't remember giving it to me?

133
00:18:19,700 --> 00:18:20,730
Momo gave it to you?

134
00:18:23,970 --> 00:18:25,000
Who are you?

135
00:18:27,810 --> 00:18:29,110
Are you playing dumb?

136
00:18:31,940 --> 00:18:32,940
The key...

137
00:18:34,310 --> 00:18:35,850
Did you get it from Momo?

138
00:18:42,750 --> 00:18:43,990
Give me the key and leave.

139
00:18:45,220 --> 00:18:46,420
Call security.

140
00:19:03,780 --> 00:19:04,840
Who was that?

141
00:19:16,220 --> 00:19:18,420
(Kim Gwang Cheol)

142
00:19:20,130 --> 00:19:21,760
(Message: Kim Gwang Cheol)

143
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:26,730
Are you on a trip?
Aren't you worried about your old man?

144
00:19:27,070 --> 00:19:28,330
I had surgery for stomach cancer.

145
00:19:30,340 --> 00:19:33,000
To get away from her father,
Jin Ju used me...

146
00:20:06,200 --> 00:20:07,240
That little...

147
00:20:08,740 --> 00:20:10,910
She swapped bodies with Geum Ba Ra.

148
00:20:15,980 --> 00:20:17,720
(CCTV recording in progress)

149
00:20:24,160 --> 00:20:25,990
Is the owner of this house...

150
00:20:26,460 --> 00:20:27,960
still not out of the hospital yet?

151
00:20:28,430 --> 00:20:31,030
- Who are you?
- She's friends with my daughter.

152
00:20:31,100 --> 00:20:32,100
But you haven't heard?

153
00:20:32,760 --> 00:20:34,100
She passed away a little while ago.

154
00:20:36,230 --> 00:20:38,500
- In a car accident?
- No.

155
00:20:39,040 --> 00:20:40,770
Apparently, something went wrong
with her brain surgery.

156
00:20:41,510 --> 00:20:42,770
I can't believe it either.

157
00:20:58,960 --> 00:21:00,190
Kim Jin Ju.

158
00:21:01,360 --> 00:21:03,260
Stabbing me in the back
until the very end...

159
00:21:38,330 --> 00:21:41,800
(Like father, like daughter...)

160
00:22:05,490 --> 00:22:07,760
Evil can never triumph over good.

161
00:22:09,330 --> 00:22:11,630
Even a single ray of light
can illuminate the darkness.

162
00:22:12,600 --> 00:22:14,970
But no matter how much you try
to shroud the light in darkness,

163
00:22:15,700 --> 00:22:17,640
you can never blot it out.

164
00:22:50,030 --> 00:22:51,170
I'm not sure...

165
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:55,370
how I'm supposed to address you.

166
00:22:57,240 --> 00:23:00,550
The shelf collapsed,
and a diary accidentally fell open.

167
00:23:01,380 --> 00:23:02,580
The name...

168
00:23:03,280 --> 00:23:05,750
Hyun Ran Hee, Momo's mother,
caught my eye.

169
00:23:07,550 --> 00:23:09,290
Let me get straight to the point.

170
00:23:11,090 --> 00:23:13,260
The long-lost daughter
you've been searching for...

171
00:23:14,360 --> 00:23:15,460
is me,

172
00:23:16,190 --> 00:23:17,460
Geum Ba Ra.

173
00:23:20,130 --> 00:23:21,670
In one of the album photos,

174
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:26,540
I saw a woman
who I thought looked a lot like me...

175
00:23:26,770 --> 00:23:28,840
and could've been an aunt.

176
00:23:29,710 --> 00:23:33,340
On the off-chance, I found a toothbrush,
a comb, and some hair,

177
00:23:33,850 --> 00:23:35,910
and I sent them for a DNA test.

178
00:23:37,480 --> 00:23:38,980
It came back as a match.

179
00:23:39,880 --> 00:23:41,990
I couldn't believe it,
so I checked again and again.

180
00:23:42,550 --> 00:23:45,090
Seeing the undeniable result,
I burst into tears.

181
00:23:46,590 --> 00:23:47,590
Father.

182
00:23:48,330 --> 00:23:49,330
Dad.

183
00:23:50,830 --> 00:23:51,830
"Dad."

184
00:23:52,900 --> 00:23:54,230
It's something...

185
00:23:55,230 --> 00:23:58,100
I've missed and desperately longed to say.

186
00:23:59,740 --> 00:24:00,940
So please...

187
00:24:02,310 --> 00:24:03,740
don't blame yourself anymore.

188
00:24:06,510 --> 00:24:08,010
I had a baby,

189
00:24:08,550 --> 00:24:09,550
a son.

190
00:24:11,180 --> 00:24:13,550
I ate the sea bream seaweed soup
that you made...

191
00:24:15,390 --> 00:24:17,560
with tears of joy.

192
00:24:18,990 --> 00:24:21,290
And thanks to you,
I've recovered well from childbirth.

193
00:24:23,390 --> 00:24:25,200
I'm so relieved and happy...

194
00:24:25,700 --> 00:24:28,430
to know who my mother...

195
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:30,370
and father were...

196
00:24:31,200 --> 00:24:32,370
before I leave.

197
00:24:35,310 --> 00:24:36,570
I have no regrets.

198
00:24:37,740 --> 00:24:39,310
Please forgive me...

199
00:24:40,010 --> 00:24:42,750
for leaving without seeing you...

200
00:24:43,180 --> 00:24:44,450
or giving you one last hug.

201
00:24:45,320 --> 00:24:47,020
Please, try to accept this.

202
00:24:48,320 --> 00:24:52,360
Still, we met a few times,
so we'll always have those memories.

203
00:24:53,290 --> 00:24:55,190
Knowing that you're my father,

204
00:24:55,860 --> 00:24:58,000
I'm so happy.

205
00:24:58,600 --> 00:24:59,830
So very happy.

206
00:25:02,700 --> 00:25:03,940
Looking at your paintings,

207
00:25:04,800 --> 00:25:06,370
my heart and my soul...

208
00:25:07,140 --> 00:25:09,270
were filled with tears of love.

209
00:25:11,140 --> 00:25:13,310
I knew exactly what you were feeling
when you painted them,

210
00:25:13,880 --> 00:25:15,280
and it truly moved me.

211
00:25:17,180 --> 00:25:19,450
Because I have always felt the same way.

212
00:25:21,450 --> 00:25:24,660
Momo will explain the rest.

213
00:25:25,190 --> 00:25:28,930
Please consider Momo
as your second daughter.

214
00:25:30,760 --> 00:25:32,600
I respect you as an artist,

215
00:25:33,900 --> 00:25:35,670
and I love you as my father.

216
00:26:01,230 --> 00:26:02,430
How did this happen?

217
00:26:07,470 --> 00:26:09,630
Did you know she was your sister?

218
00:26:13,740 --> 00:26:14,740
Yes.

219
00:26:18,210 --> 00:26:20,510
I heard what happened to the reporter,
Geum Ba Ra.

220
00:26:24,180 --> 00:26:27,620
You see, I actually met her
before my daughter did.

221
00:26:27,890 --> 00:26:29,990
Things like this make you think
there's no deity.

222
00:26:30,660 --> 00:26:32,290
Of all the people to take...

223
00:26:33,730 --> 00:26:35,730
Was it really a cerebral hemorrhage?

224
00:26:37,060 --> 00:26:38,260
Yes.

225
00:26:38,460 --> 00:26:40,100
She seemed perfectly fine.

226
00:26:42,030 --> 00:26:45,100
Then, that girl is gone for good.

227
00:26:47,170 --> 00:26:48,310
Could I get some water?

228
00:27:01,820 --> 00:27:03,390
Who performed the surgery?

229
00:27:04,320 --> 00:27:05,760
Director Shin Ju Shin?

230
00:27:06,990 --> 00:27:07,990
Yes.

231
00:27:08,860 --> 00:27:10,760
They were both in their prime.
It's such a senseless loss.

232
00:27:11,860 --> 00:27:14,830
A part of me wonders if Jin Ju was lonely
and decided to take her along.

233
00:27:22,770 --> 00:27:25,240
He's your one and only grandson.

234
00:27:27,410 --> 00:27:28,450
What's his name?

235
00:27:33,420 --> 00:27:34,720
(Exam Room One,
Neurosurgery Director Shin Ju Shin)

236
00:27:50,400 --> 00:27:53,070
Please, I'm terrified of my dad.

237
00:27:53,710 --> 00:27:54,710
Please...

238
00:27:54,840 --> 00:27:55,970
I want to try...

239
00:27:56,840 --> 00:27:58,340
living as Momo.

240
00:28:30,440 --> 00:28:33,580
Where is Director Shin?
He's not answering his phone.

241
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:56,370
Your husband is here.

242
00:29:09,010 --> 00:29:10,010
The baby.

243
00:29:17,990 --> 00:29:19,720
Why were both of your phones turned off?

244
00:29:22,330 --> 00:29:24,030
You haven't cleared out Ba Ra's place yet,
have you?

245
00:29:29,070 --> 00:29:30,070
I'll take care of it.

246
00:29:30,900 --> 00:29:32,440
She asked me to.

247
00:29:34,110 --> 00:29:35,770
Even so,
can you clear out her entire place?

248
00:29:36,670 --> 00:29:37,780
You don't have time for that.

249
00:29:38,040 --> 00:29:39,110
I can make time.

250
00:29:40,610 --> 00:29:41,780
Do you have time?

251
00:29:44,450 --> 00:29:45,820
Do you have time?

252
00:29:50,920 --> 00:29:51,920
Who is that?

253
00:29:52,290 --> 00:29:53,460
My manager.

254
00:29:54,290 --> 00:29:55,460
Planning a comeback?

255
00:29:56,090 --> 00:29:58,860
No, I just need someone to help me out.

256
00:30:01,470 --> 00:30:02,970
Why are you so down?

257
00:30:03,800 --> 00:30:06,000
I thought deep down
you'd be happy about this.

258
00:30:08,040 --> 00:30:09,710
You never felt this way about her.

259
00:30:15,280 --> 00:30:17,050
Ba Ra's door code.

260
00:30:19,380 --> 00:30:20,720
I'm going to buy the apartment...

261
00:30:21,320 --> 00:30:22,620
and use it as my studio.

262
00:30:38,570 --> 00:30:39,900
It's 1210, star.

263
00:30:45,340 --> 00:30:46,980
Is that the code Ba Ra set?

264
00:30:50,720 --> 00:30:52,180
That's my birthday...

265
00:31:09,470 --> 00:31:10,670
Is there someone in there?

266
00:31:13,440 --> 00:31:14,440
No.

267
00:31:22,380 --> 00:31:23,850
I'm going to do what I have to do.

268
00:31:49,340 --> 00:31:50,340
Yong Joong must be...

269
00:31:50,940 --> 00:31:51,940
the dad.

270
00:32:11,360 --> 00:32:13,060
(Yong Joong)

271
00:32:35,490 --> 00:32:36,620
How did you get in here?

272
00:32:43,230 --> 00:32:45,060
You're supposed to wear a swimsuit
at the pool.

273
00:32:47,370 --> 00:32:49,270
Jin Ju's father came to see me.

274
00:32:52,140 --> 00:32:54,570
She proposed the surgery
just to get away from her father.

275
00:32:55,040 --> 00:32:56,870
I saw a 300,000 dollar transfer
in her account.

276
00:32:56,870 --> 00:32:58,110
Sounds just like Kim Jin Ju.

277
00:32:59,840 --> 00:33:01,680
It's true what they say,
people don't change.

278
00:33:02,780 --> 00:33:04,420
I had no idea.

279
00:33:05,350 --> 00:33:07,120
All this time, I just felt sorry for her.

280
00:33:08,690 --> 00:33:11,020
Looks like you already know who I am,

281
00:33:11,960 --> 00:33:13,420
seeing how you haven't asked.

282
00:33:15,560 --> 00:33:17,900
My daughter gave me your number.

283
00:33:17,960 --> 00:33:21,130
She said you, Director Shin Ju Shin,
with your world-shocking skills,

284
00:33:21,630 --> 00:33:23,900
made her into Momo.

285
00:33:26,140 --> 00:33:27,510
So what did you do with her body?

286
00:33:29,340 --> 00:33:30,440
My daughter's body.

287
00:33:31,980 --> 00:33:34,180
- Jin Ju.
- Please, have a seat.

288
00:33:45,090 --> 00:33:46,260
Answer me.

289
00:33:46,890 --> 00:33:49,330
If you put her brain in Momo's body,

290
00:33:50,190 --> 00:33:51,930
what did you do with her body?

291
00:33:53,930 --> 00:33:54,930
I don't know.

292
00:33:56,430 --> 00:33:58,440
- You don't know?
- I just did the surgery.

293
00:33:59,670 --> 00:34:00,670
My staff handled it.

294
00:34:03,270 --> 00:34:04,480
Who on your staff?

295
00:34:05,480 --> 00:34:06,480
Give me a name.

296
00:34:09,380 --> 00:34:11,750
You threw her away as medical waste,
didn't you?

297
00:34:12,320 --> 00:34:13,450
Where?

298
00:34:18,860 --> 00:34:20,790
I noticed Momo was different again.

299
00:34:21,990 --> 00:34:22,990
Who is it this time?

300
00:34:27,000 --> 00:34:28,100
Aren't you going to answer me?

301
00:34:32,540 --> 00:34:34,270
Is it Reporter Geum Ba Ra?

302
00:34:37,510 --> 00:34:39,980
You swapped their brains again.

303
00:34:41,380 --> 00:34:45,150
Is my daughter, Kim Jin Ju, dead?

304
00:34:45,550 --> 00:34:46,820
For good?

305
00:34:48,450 --> 00:34:49,850
Is she dead?

306
00:35:56,120 --> 00:35:57,690
My daughter!

307
00:36:30,820 --> 00:36:32,090
He's stabbing the Director!

308
00:40:38,170 --> 00:40:39,270
Ba Ra.

309
00:40:48,180 --> 00:40:49,180
Geum Ba Ra.

310
00:40:57,490 --> 00:41:00,590
(Nua General Hospital)

311
00:41:02,090 --> 00:41:05,200
The person you've called is unavailable.
Please leave a message after the tone.

312
00:41:05,260 --> 00:41:07,000
(Director Shin Ju Shin)

313
00:41:07,100 --> 00:41:11,870
(Hospital Director, Shin Ju Shin)

314
00:41:12,870 --> 00:41:14,870
- Is the Director...
- He must be sick.

315
00:41:14,940 --> 00:41:16,870
- He's not in yet?
- No.

316
00:41:51,910 --> 00:41:55,480
Hello? This is the 21st floor
of Nua General Hospital.

317
00:41:55,550 --> 00:41:56,980
There's a dead body here!

318
00:42:00,250 --> 00:42:03,350
(Nua General Hospital)

319
00:42:09,860 --> 00:42:12,530
I think it's a patient
we operated on recently.

320
00:42:12,600 --> 00:42:14,730
- And the Director isn't here?
- No, sir.

321
00:42:28,980 --> 00:42:29,980
You...

322
00:42:38,190 --> 00:42:39,360
No.

323
00:42:43,590 --> 00:42:45,230
Nurse Lee! Don't!

324
00:43:02,710 --> 00:43:03,910
Director Shin!

325
00:43:25,570 --> 00:43:27,070
He kept grilling me with questions.

326
00:43:27,070 --> 00:43:28,540
"Did Geum Ba Ra have brain surgery?"

327
00:43:28,610 --> 00:43:30,010
"Did Director Shin perform
the surgery himself?"

328
00:43:31,980 --> 00:43:33,840
What if he wasn't
Kim Jin Ju's biological father,

329
00:43:33,910 --> 00:43:35,110
but Ba Ra's instead?

330
00:43:37,480 --> 00:43:40,550
There's no other reason
he'd snap and kill him like that.

331
00:43:45,560 --> 00:43:48,490
(Our deepest condolences to the family,
The Staff of Nua Funeral Home)

332
00:44:00,040 --> 00:44:01,740
You'll live longer
with a little imperfection.

333
00:44:02,140 --> 00:44:03,670
And I take it you don't, Director Shin?

334
00:44:04,410 --> 00:44:05,580
I guess I'm not long for this world, then.

335
00:44:13,950 --> 00:44:15,490
I didn't see it myself,

336
00:44:17,620 --> 00:44:18,620
but at home...

337
00:44:50,490 --> 00:44:53,560
Border Collies, Jindo dogs,
Chow Chows, Tibetan Mastiffs...

338
00:44:54,090 --> 00:44:55,790
You can have all the dogs you want,

339
00:44:55,790 --> 00:44:58,360
and we can live here, together.

340
00:44:58,500 --> 00:45:01,060
I'm always grateful. I really am.

341
00:45:01,130 --> 00:45:02,500
Then get rid of that feeling,
starting now.

342
00:45:03,670 --> 00:45:05,070
I'm not lacking for anything,

343
00:45:06,140 --> 00:45:07,500
and I'm tired of being thanked.

344
00:45:08,140 --> 00:45:10,370
I don't care for effort
born from obligation.

345
00:45:10,840 --> 00:45:12,280
I'm not forcing myself.

346
00:45:12,710 --> 00:45:13,710
Regardless.

347
00:45:15,950 --> 00:45:17,610
Want me to look for a purebred Retriever?

348
00:45:24,120 --> 00:45:25,360
You transferred 300,000 dollars.

349
00:45:25,890 --> 00:45:27,560
- That's right.
- Were you being blackmailed?

350
00:45:27,620 --> 00:45:30,360
No. Why would I be blackmailed?

351
00:45:30,730 --> 00:45:33,830
He said he didn't know how to go on
after Jin Ju died.

352
00:45:34,530 --> 00:45:36,600
Jin Ju was always really good to me.

353
00:45:37,030 --> 00:45:39,140
I sent it to him
as a sort of severance package.

354
00:45:39,470 --> 00:45:40,540
But 300,000 dollars?

355
00:45:40,740 --> 00:45:41,740
Yes.

356
00:45:43,140 --> 00:45:46,540
He said he couldn't get a job anywhere
because of his record.

357
00:45:58,020 --> 00:46:00,520
We had so many memories together
in this house.

358
00:46:01,890 --> 00:46:04,390
All those meals your mother made
for us here.

359
00:46:06,060 --> 00:46:09,170
You'd hate this house going to another.
I know I would.

360
00:46:12,940 --> 00:46:14,170
Did you meet Ba Ra?

361
00:46:17,840 --> 00:46:19,080
Of course you did.

362
00:46:23,410 --> 00:46:25,150
("Fearless Love")

363
00:46:49,010 --> 00:46:50,810
("Fearless Love")

364
00:46:52,740 --> 00:46:53,740
(Momo)

365
00:46:58,110 --> 00:46:59,120
Hello.

366
00:46:59,380 --> 00:47:01,790
Are you just going to neglect
Yong Joong like that?

367
00:47:03,120 --> 00:47:06,920
Did you know he moved
into Reporter Geum's apartment?

368
00:47:09,560 --> 00:47:11,730
Reporter Geum is gone,
Director Shin is gone...

369
00:47:12,060 --> 00:47:13,500
Now it's just the two of you.

370
00:47:14,230 --> 00:47:15,700
You only have each other now.

371
00:47:19,240 --> 00:47:22,970
Men have a certain kind of pride
that women can't understand...

372
00:47:23,070 --> 00:47:25,910
And women don't? We have our pride too.

373
00:47:26,380 --> 00:47:28,250
Just think of her as his first love.

374
00:47:29,510 --> 00:47:32,620
He's a good guy with a big heart,
so he can't just let her go easily.

375
00:47:33,680 --> 00:47:35,220
Even though you're younger,

376
00:47:35,750 --> 00:47:37,820
be the bigger person and take care of him.

377
00:47:38,460 --> 00:47:39,760
Tell him you want to make things work.

378
00:47:40,360 --> 00:47:42,890
He'll be so grateful,
he'll be the most loyal husband ever.

379
00:47:43,360 --> 00:47:44,430
I guarantee it.

380
00:48:36,310 --> 00:48:37,350
Yong Joong.

381
00:48:38,550 --> 00:48:39,780
Don't let this get you down.

382
00:48:54,160 --> 00:48:55,170
Ba Ra.

383
00:49:05,640 --> 00:49:06,640
(James)

384
00:49:10,080 --> 00:49:12,020
- Hey.
- Where are you? Home?

385
00:49:12,420 --> 00:49:14,220
- No.
- You are not going to believe this.

386
00:49:14,350 --> 00:49:16,290
I'm on my way to your house,
so run there...

387
00:49:16,650 --> 00:49:17,720
at the speed of light.

388
00:49:56,560 --> 00:49:58,530
I wonder if Paul Kim has arrived yet.

389
00:50:07,500 --> 00:50:08,610
(Artist Paul Kim)

390
00:50:12,440 --> 00:50:14,310
Hello, Mr. Ha.

391
00:50:14,610 --> 00:50:15,610
Hello.

392
00:50:16,180 --> 00:50:18,450
Are you still in Germany?

393
00:50:18,950 --> 00:50:19,950
No, I'm back.

394
00:50:20,850 --> 00:50:21,850
When did you get back?

395
00:50:23,750 --> 00:50:25,190
Do I hear a baby crying?

396
00:50:26,560 --> 00:50:27,560
It's my grandson.

397
00:50:28,830 --> 00:50:29,830
Your grandson?

398
00:50:30,130 --> 00:50:31,260
I found my daughter.

399
00:50:33,000 --> 00:50:35,730
But it's a long story.

400
00:50:35,930 --> 00:50:37,470
You were bound to find out anyway.

401
00:50:38,330 --> 00:50:40,200
I'm at Momo's place right now.

402
00:50:43,110 --> 00:50:45,440
You're saying Reporter Geum Ba Ra
was your long-lost daughter?

403
00:50:46,140 --> 00:50:47,140
Yes.

404
00:50:52,050 --> 00:50:53,780
At least she had the baby
before she passed away.

405
00:50:54,320 --> 00:50:56,820
So the baby's mother is Reporter Geum?

406
00:50:57,620 --> 00:50:58,620
Yes.

407
00:50:59,790 --> 00:51:01,020
Is it a boy or a girl?

408
00:51:02,390 --> 00:51:04,460
- It's a boy.
- When was he born?

409
00:51:04,690 --> 00:51:05,860
He's almost three months old.

410
00:51:08,530 --> 00:51:09,630
And who's the father?

411
00:51:10,170 --> 00:51:11,170
I don't know.

412
00:51:17,640 --> 00:51:18,680
Go and have your dinner.

413
00:51:22,410 --> 00:51:24,150
So you didn't know
anything about it either?

414
00:51:27,420 --> 00:51:28,420
What is it?

415
00:51:28,790 --> 00:51:29,790
Goodness.

416
00:51:32,220 --> 00:51:34,190
He's your son, no doubt about it.

417
00:51:34,190 --> 00:51:38,190
He's a carbon copy of you
when you were a baby.

418
00:51:38,190 --> 00:51:40,200
Did he really say Ba Ra had a baby?

419
00:51:40,200 --> 00:51:41,330
Yes.

420
00:51:41,330 --> 00:51:42,400
The situation...

421
00:51:42,830 --> 00:51:46,470
I mean, Reporter Geum and Momo
are half-sisters who share a mother.

422
00:51:48,270 --> 00:51:49,410
I've never seen anything like this.

423
00:51:49,610 --> 00:51:51,640
You don't even need a DNA test.

424
00:51:52,540 --> 00:51:54,210
She must have disappeared
after she found out she was pregnant.

425
00:51:55,310 --> 00:51:56,710
Poor Reporter Geum...

426
00:51:56,710 --> 00:51:57,980
How could she die...

427
00:51:58,380 --> 00:52:00,050
and leave her newborn?

428
00:52:09,330 --> 00:52:10,790
We have to bring him here and raise him.

429
00:52:10,790 --> 00:52:13,160
I know it sounds like a soap opera,

430
00:52:13,230 --> 00:52:14,230
Reporter Geum, Momo...

431
00:52:14,500 --> 00:52:18,870
I told Momo to get back with you
because she seemed different.

432
00:52:20,770 --> 00:52:21,770
Are you going to see for yourself?

433
00:52:23,140 --> 00:52:24,570
Let's go together. We'll take my car.

434
00:52:25,340 --> 00:52:26,410
You've already seen him.

435
00:52:27,940 --> 00:52:29,180
I want to see him again.

436
00:52:34,250 --> 00:52:36,250
They say the world is big and small,

437
00:52:36,250 --> 00:52:38,660
but who would've thought it was Paul Kim?

438
00:52:40,190 --> 00:52:42,430
He spent all that time
desperately searching for his daughter.

439
00:52:46,100 --> 00:52:49,100
Poor Reporter Geum,
and the baby, of course.

440
00:52:50,130 --> 00:52:51,230
This is crazy...

441
00:53:00,310 --> 00:53:02,210
It's not something
that needs to be a secret.

442
00:53:02,650 --> 00:53:04,080
He asked whose baby it was,

443
00:53:04,710 --> 00:53:05,980
and there was no reason to lie.

444
00:53:07,220 --> 00:53:08,220
Right.

445
00:53:10,750 --> 00:53:12,720
You should've seen
how shocked he looked...

446
00:53:13,660 --> 00:53:14,660
after seeing the baby.

447
00:53:15,360 --> 00:53:17,190
I guess he never saw it coming?

448
00:53:18,800 --> 00:53:20,360
I had no idea we would end up
connected like this,

449
00:53:21,100 --> 00:53:23,430
and I've been pretty close
with James Ha this whole time.

450
00:53:26,170 --> 00:53:27,300
I should have introduced myself sooner.

451
00:53:28,040 --> 00:53:29,070
I'm Ha Yong Joong.

452
00:53:30,210 --> 00:53:32,240
- You don't have to...
- Take it.

453
00:53:35,410 --> 00:53:36,650
Sorry to bother you so late.

454
00:53:37,210 --> 00:53:38,620
How about some rooibos tea?

455
00:53:38,750 --> 00:53:40,720
No, I'm fine.
I don't feel like having anything.

456
00:53:41,150 --> 00:53:42,150
Please, have a seat.

457
00:53:46,490 --> 00:53:47,490
Is the baby asleep?

458
00:53:47,760 --> 00:53:50,630
- He's having some formula.
- Eat and sleep, that's all he does.

459
00:53:51,560 --> 00:53:53,030
He's not awake for very long.

460
00:53:53,260 --> 00:53:55,600
He probably won't start crawling
until he's 8 or 9 months old.

461
00:53:59,470 --> 00:54:01,940
So you were close with my daughter too?

462
00:54:08,650 --> 00:54:09,650
Yes.

463
00:54:18,250 --> 00:54:19,260
Hello?

464
00:54:20,260 --> 00:54:21,260
Really?

465
00:54:23,130 --> 00:54:24,130
Thank you.

466
00:54:25,800 --> 00:54:28,100
I'll be home in a bit. Yes.

467
00:54:32,270 --> 00:54:34,540
That was a neighbor,
saying the lights are on at my house.

468
00:54:35,770 --> 00:54:37,140
I was so excited to see my grandson...

469
00:54:37,740 --> 00:54:39,110
that I rushed out, leaving the lights on.

470
00:54:40,380 --> 00:54:42,450
Could you please explain
in a bit more detail?

471
00:54:42,910 --> 00:54:44,250
What exactly happened?

472
00:54:53,120 --> 00:54:54,120
Not now.

473
00:54:57,130 --> 00:54:59,930
Honestly, it still doesn't feel real.

474
00:55:08,540 --> 00:55:10,640
There's this letter,

475
00:55:11,440 --> 00:55:12,840
and the DNA test results.

476
00:55:21,880 --> 00:55:23,350
Is that Reporter Geum's hair?

477
00:55:24,550 --> 00:55:25,560
Yes.

478
00:55:26,460 --> 00:55:29,060
- Couldn't it have been malpractice?
- No.

479
00:55:30,130 --> 00:55:33,000
Director Shin Ju Shin is
a leading authority on brain surgery.

480
00:55:33,830 --> 00:55:34,960
That is true.

481
00:55:38,170 --> 00:55:41,900
I'll be sure to come by
and pay my respects properly soon.

482
00:55:45,910 --> 00:55:48,410
In any case, we're officially family now.

483
00:55:49,080 --> 00:55:50,080
I suppose we are.

484
00:55:50,450 --> 00:55:53,320
I'll set something up for us all
to get together properly.

485
00:57:55,510 --> 00:57:56,770
He's your son, right?

486
00:58:00,680 --> 00:58:02,710
It's not right for him
to be living with his aunt.

487
00:58:03,050 --> 00:58:04,450
We should be the ones raising him.

488
00:58:05,880 --> 00:58:07,380
When Momo finds out everything,

489
00:58:07,920 --> 00:58:08,990
think about Paul Kim...

490
00:58:10,720 --> 00:58:12,360
It's something I have
to face sooner or later.

491
00:58:15,260 --> 00:58:16,990
Before we officially started dating,

492
00:58:19,900 --> 00:58:21,430
I spent one night with Ba Ra.

493
00:58:23,830 --> 00:58:25,300
I didn't know she got pregnant,

494
00:58:27,000 --> 00:58:29,270
and I think she left
because of a misunderstanding.

495
00:58:31,870 --> 00:58:32,880
What misunderstanding?

496
00:58:33,810 --> 00:58:34,910
It's hard to explain.

497
00:58:37,180 --> 00:58:39,180
It's just putting your thoughts
into words.

498
00:58:39,650 --> 00:58:40,650
Is it that hard?

499
00:58:43,390 --> 00:58:44,490
Ba Ra is the one who needs to hear it.

500
00:58:46,820 --> 00:58:47,820
But she's not here, is she?

501
00:58:52,430 --> 00:58:54,400
We met again after 15 years
for an interview.

502
00:58:56,870 --> 00:59:00,600
If I hadn't realized she was the kid
I knew growing up,

503
00:59:02,240 --> 00:59:04,770
we might have started dating.
Or at least, I think so.

504
00:59:07,610 --> 00:59:09,910
I could vaguely sense
a certain longing in her,

505
00:59:11,910 --> 00:59:13,420
but at the same time,
she was so self-assured.

506
00:59:15,180 --> 00:59:16,190
It was refreshing.

507
00:59:21,990 --> 00:59:22,990
Anyway,

508
00:59:24,430 --> 00:59:26,300
the next day,
I had to go on a business trip abroad,

509
00:59:29,400 --> 00:59:31,600
and I was hit with this feeling
that I'd done something terrible.

510
00:59:33,600 --> 00:59:35,570
I kept picturing Ba Ra's face
as a little girl,

511
00:59:36,770 --> 00:59:37,770
and I was so confused.

512
00:59:39,840 --> 00:59:41,540
I couldn't marry her
in that state of mind,

513
00:59:42,210 --> 00:59:43,680
so I asked her for some time.

514
00:59:47,880 --> 00:59:49,290
But I think she must have misunderstood.

515
00:59:57,030 --> 00:59:59,000
"Just another rejection."

516
01:00:00,660 --> 01:00:02,130
She must have thought that.

517
01:00:12,910 --> 01:00:14,040
I guess it's because you're sisters.

518
01:00:15,340 --> 01:00:17,110
It feels just like I'm talking to Ba Ra.

519
01:00:17,950 --> 01:00:19,280
I never noticed it before.

520
01:00:24,990 --> 01:00:25,990
So...

521
01:00:27,060 --> 01:00:28,790
we need to file the divorce papers
as planned.

522
01:00:29,590 --> 01:00:30,830
This isn't right.

523
01:00:33,160 --> 01:00:34,460
I'll raise Bi.

524
01:00:34,860 --> 01:00:36,170
She asked me to take care of him.

525
01:00:36,170 --> 01:00:37,700
He's better with his dad
than with his aunt.

526
01:00:38,570 --> 01:00:39,940
I'm confident I can raise him well.

527
01:00:39,940 --> 01:00:40,970
And let a stepmother raise him?

528
01:00:41,270 --> 01:00:43,370
I'm not getting married again to anyone.

529
01:00:49,050 --> 01:00:50,050
Just like how my brother...

530
01:00:50,880 --> 01:00:52,180
raised me...

531
01:00:53,450 --> 01:00:55,150
I'll make sure he never feels the void
of not having a mother.

532
01:00:56,490 --> 01:00:59,190
I'm confident I can raise him with love.

533
01:01:03,890 --> 01:01:04,890
Please.

534
01:01:07,760 --> 01:01:09,870
Honestly, I wasn't a very good husband.

535
01:01:13,640 --> 01:01:15,070
After his 100-day celebration,

536
01:01:15,970 --> 01:01:16,970
you can take him.

537
01:01:21,980 --> 01:01:22,980
Thank you.

538
01:01:23,450 --> 01:01:25,480
We'll file the papers after that.

539
01:01:35,490 --> 01:01:37,660
I'm going to register him as Geum Bi.

540
01:01:39,600 --> 01:01:41,900
Ha Geum Bi.

541
01:01:44,170 --> 01:01:46,270
Ha Geum Bi.

542
01:01:49,740 --> 01:01:52,240
- Hello.
- Right. This room...

543
01:01:52,240 --> 01:01:54,340
No, wait, in that room over there, please.

544
01:01:54,680 --> 01:01:55,680
Got it.

545
01:01:57,510 --> 01:01:59,220
Let's see, what else...

546
01:02:01,680 --> 01:02:03,450
Maybe I should've redone the wallpaper.

547
01:02:08,460 --> 01:02:09,930
It's not your fault, Yong Joong.

548
01:02:13,500 --> 01:02:16,470
It was probably from the shock
after his business failed,

549
01:02:18,130 --> 01:02:20,440
but my father also died of
a brain hemorrhage just eight days later.

550
01:02:26,610 --> 01:02:27,740
And I'm sure,

551
01:02:29,280 --> 01:02:30,510
Ba Ra didn't have any resentment.

552
01:02:32,780 --> 01:02:33,780
If anything,

553
01:02:34,820 --> 01:02:37,020
I think she was grateful.

554
01:02:48,860 --> 01:02:51,600
(I'm not sure
how I'm supposed to address you.)

555
01:02:54,870 --> 01:02:56,340
Still, you had it better than I did.

556
01:02:57,940 --> 01:03:00,840
I never got to see her grow up.

557
01:03:01,610 --> 01:03:03,410
Or even hold her hand once.

558
01:03:03,750 --> 01:03:04,750
All I got...

559
01:03:05,150 --> 01:03:08,680
was meeting her a few times
as an artist and a reporter.

560
01:03:11,120 --> 01:03:12,520
Why don't you come live with us?

561
01:03:17,330 --> 01:03:18,330
Whenever you're ready.

562
01:03:19,400 --> 01:03:22,230
I think having his grandfather around...

563
01:03:22,770 --> 01:03:24,230
would be so much better
for Geum Bi emotionally.

564
01:03:27,970 --> 01:03:30,640
- I'll visit often, if it's no trouble.
- Trouble? Of course not.

565
01:03:31,740 --> 01:03:33,140
You're my father-in-law.

566
01:03:35,040 --> 01:03:37,780
I'm curious about
how he and my mother met,

567
01:03:38,110 --> 01:03:39,420
but he won't tell me.

568
01:03:42,920 --> 01:03:43,920
You know, don't you?

569
01:03:44,450 --> 01:03:45,790
I heard you know the whole story.

570
01:03:45,860 --> 01:03:47,760
It's probably hard for him to tell you.

571
01:03:48,060 --> 01:03:49,790
It's not like they ended on good terms.

572
01:03:50,990 --> 01:03:52,190
But that's all in the past now.

573
01:03:55,560 --> 01:03:57,330
They met back in high school.

574
01:03:57,630 --> 01:03:59,840
CEO Hyun was a year older. She was 20.

575
01:04:00,570 --> 01:04:02,910
She dropped out of her freshman year
to have the baby.

576
01:04:03,640 --> 01:04:06,610
At the time, I think Paul's family
suddenly went bankrupt.

577
01:04:07,310 --> 01:04:10,010
Maybe that's why, but I heard
she left the baby and just disappeared.

578
01:04:11,150 --> 01:04:12,580
I don't know for sure,

579
01:04:12,780 --> 01:04:15,120
but he said even her mother
didn't know where she was.

580
01:04:16,820 --> 01:04:18,790
He said she was a newborn,
not even ten days old.

581
01:04:26,330 --> 01:04:29,670
If Reporter Geum were still with us,
you would be sisters again.

582
01:04:29,970 --> 01:04:31,400
It would be a perfect happy ending.

583
01:04:32,740 --> 01:04:34,170
But when I think of...

584
01:04:34,170 --> 01:04:36,340
Yong Joong and Geum Bi
spending their whole lives missing you...

585
01:04:37,140 --> 01:04:39,640
No matter how hard we all try,
no matter how well...

586
01:04:40,340 --> 01:04:41,810
we raise him,

587
01:04:42,340 --> 01:04:43,610
that void left by his mother...

588
01:04:44,750 --> 01:04:45,810
I know what that's like.

589
01:04:48,420 --> 01:04:51,390
The necklace I put on her,
engraved with her name and birthday,

590
01:04:52,290 --> 01:04:53,960
must have broken or fallen off,

591
01:04:54,320 --> 01:04:57,490
and ended up in Kim Gwang Cheol's
daughter's swaddling blanket.

592
01:04:58,360 --> 01:04:59,830
That's how they got switched.

593
01:05:00,700 --> 01:05:02,730
They were both taken to Minjin Church
on the same day.

594
01:05:08,000 --> 01:05:11,210
You could just raise Geum Bi together.

595
01:05:12,740 --> 01:05:15,140
It's not like the whole world knows
our family's private business.

596
01:05:16,650 --> 01:05:19,350
That kind of thing happened
from time to time back in the day.

597
01:05:24,890 --> 01:05:26,760
Ready? Smile!

598
01:05:27,720 --> 01:05:30,930
A bigger smile now. Show me your teeth.

599
01:05:30,930 --> 01:05:31,960
Look at you.

600
01:05:31,960 --> 01:05:35,660
Everyone, let's give Geum Bi a big hand!
One, two!

601
01:05:36,870 --> 01:05:38,670
Great. That looks very natural.

602
01:05:38,770 --> 01:05:42,270
(To my beloved baby,
May you grow up beautiful and healthy)

603
01:05:43,570 --> 01:05:45,980
The chef would like to know
how you're enjoying your meal.

604
01:05:46,540 --> 01:05:48,880
Please tell the chef it is excellent...

605
01:05:48,880 --> 01:05:50,650
- and thank him for the special care.
- I will.

606
01:05:51,510 --> 01:05:54,420
Next time, let's go somewhere more casual
so we can bring Geum Bi.

607
01:05:54,480 --> 01:05:57,520
That's right. So many decent places
don't allow kids these days.

608
01:05:58,250 --> 01:06:00,020
Mr. Kim, I'll get it next time.

609
01:06:00,960 --> 01:06:01,960
Sure.

610
01:06:04,230 --> 01:06:06,000
Now that you're leaving showbiz,
what's next?

611
01:06:06,660 --> 01:06:08,560
I took over the foundation
that runs the Nua Children's Home.

612
01:06:09,200 --> 01:06:10,200
Really?

613
01:06:10,200 --> 01:06:13,600
My goal is to identify the kids' talents
and help them cultivate their strengths.

614
01:06:15,840 --> 01:06:17,670
I can help teach painting.

615
01:06:18,340 --> 01:06:19,710
That would be amazing, thank you.

616
01:06:29,620 --> 01:06:32,590
My dear daughter,
don't you worry about Geum Bi.

617
01:06:40,160 --> 01:06:42,630
Excuse me, our ambassador is a big fan...

618
01:06:42,630 --> 01:06:44,670
and was hoping he could get a picture.

619
01:06:50,410 --> 01:06:52,940
- Of course.
- This is Ms. Momo's husband.

620
01:06:56,610 --> 01:06:58,910
I'm Yong Joong Ha.
It's an honor to meet you.

621
01:06:59,050 --> 01:07:01,850
No, no, the honor is mine.
You've made quite an impression.

622
01:07:02,350 --> 01:07:05,650
Thank you, Your Excellency.
You are the one who is truly impressive.

623
01:07:06,760 --> 01:07:09,320
Let me now introduce
a fashion industry leader.

624
01:07:09,860 --> 01:07:12,430
This is James Ha, CEO of Lim Company.

625
01:07:14,760 --> 01:07:15,830
Was it last year?

626
01:07:15,830 --> 01:07:17,700
I believe we met
at a party at the Egyptian embassy.

627
01:07:17,900 --> 01:07:19,230
Perhaps it was last year.

628
01:07:19,300 --> 01:07:21,640
I think we met at a party
at the Egyptian embassy.

629
01:07:21,740 --> 01:07:23,570
- Did we?
- Goodness.

630
01:07:23,710 --> 01:07:25,610
You both have such
an amazing sense of style.

631
01:07:25,670 --> 01:07:28,310
Both of you have such
a remarkable sense of style.

632
01:07:29,480 --> 01:07:31,080
- Thank you.
- You look stunning.

633
01:07:31,080 --> 01:07:32,850
I'll make sure to stop by sometime.

634
01:07:33,220 --> 01:07:35,250
She says she'll be sure
to stop by sometime.

635
01:07:35,380 --> 01:07:36,720
It would be my honor.

636
01:07:37,490 --> 01:07:38,520
Your Excellency,

637
01:07:38,820 --> 01:07:41,160
you had an interview
with Reporter Ba Ra Geum...

638
01:07:41,220 --> 01:07:42,960
from Sungwoo Daily last year, didn't you?

639
01:07:43,490 --> 01:07:45,360
How did you know that?
Did you read the article?

640
01:07:45,360 --> 01:07:46,400
Yes.

641
01:07:46,600 --> 01:07:50,100
I was so inspired by your interview,
so I saved a copy of it.

642
01:07:50,900 --> 01:07:51,900
I'm flattered.

643
01:07:52,330 --> 01:07:53,970
It's such an honor to meet you here.

644
01:07:54,400 --> 01:07:55,640
Shall we take a picture?

645
01:07:55,900 --> 01:07:56,910
Yes, sure.

646
01:07:57,710 --> 01:07:58,940
On the count of three.

647
01:07:58,940 --> 01:08:01,740
One, two, three.

648
01:08:02,610 --> 01:08:03,680
Big smile.

649
01:08:05,410 --> 01:08:06,420
Great.

650
01:08:09,150 --> 01:08:11,090
Climb up.

651
01:08:11,090 --> 01:08:12,550
One, two,

652
01:08:13,220 --> 01:08:14,490
three, four.

653
01:08:14,490 --> 01:08:16,990
And back, one, two, three, four.

654
01:08:17,060 --> 01:08:19,500
- That's how it's done, all right?
- Yes!

655
01:08:19,830 --> 01:08:22,230
Just keep working hard.
The sky helps those who help themselves.

656
01:08:22,730 --> 01:08:24,330
We just have to give it our all.

657
01:08:24,330 --> 01:08:25,330
- Okay.
- Okay.

658
01:08:25,330 --> 01:08:26,740
All right, let's take it from the top.

659
01:08:44,850 --> 01:08:46,820
She must've secretly studied English.

660
01:08:47,020 --> 01:08:48,260
I was completely surprised.

661
01:08:51,490 --> 01:08:54,200
Anyway, you've got to give her credit.
Her whole demeanor has changed.

662
01:08:54,360 --> 01:08:55,600
She's like a whole new person.

663
01:08:58,000 --> 01:09:00,040
Our little man is awake.

664
01:09:08,640 --> 01:09:10,510
(Yong Joong)

665
01:09:17,950 --> 01:09:20,060
(Yong Joong)

666
01:09:22,760 --> 01:09:23,760
Hello?

667
01:09:24,160 --> 01:09:25,590
I've got the papers ready.

668
01:09:26,030 --> 01:09:28,000
We should probably handle this
through our lawyers, right?

669
01:09:30,000 --> 01:09:31,730
It'll be all over the news anyway.

670
01:09:32,370 --> 01:09:33,540
Let's just go together.

671
01:09:34,400 --> 01:09:35,400
To the courthouse ourselves?

672
01:09:35,700 --> 01:09:36,740
Yes.

673
01:09:36,740 --> 01:09:37,970
All right.

674
01:09:38,510 --> 01:09:39,640
When are you free?

675
01:09:41,010 --> 01:09:42,010
Tomorrow...

676
01:09:43,280 --> 01:09:44,880
Let's file them after lunch.

677
01:09:46,280 --> 01:09:47,280
Okay.

678
01:10:21,350 --> 01:10:22,650
Isn't it hard running the orphanage?

679
01:10:23,350 --> 01:10:24,490
I mean, all you've ever done is act.

680
01:10:25,490 --> 01:10:26,790
Nothing in life is ever easy.

681
01:10:34,700 --> 01:10:36,130
The kids love it, though.

682
01:10:37,400 --> 01:10:38,700
You can see the change in their eyes.

683
01:10:51,180 --> 01:10:52,180
Enjoy your meal.

684
01:10:52,580 --> 01:10:53,580
Thank you.

685
01:10:55,850 --> 01:10:58,150
Are you really not going to act anymore?

686
01:10:59,550 --> 01:11:00,560
Yes.

687
01:11:00,560 --> 01:11:03,060
Your reruns have been on a lot lately.

688
01:11:03,530 --> 01:11:05,060
They never get old.

689
01:11:12,730 --> 01:11:13,740
You're not adding vinegar?

690
01:11:15,470 --> 01:11:16,470
No.

691
01:11:16,910 --> 01:11:18,270
Ba Ra eats hers plain, too.

692
01:11:22,380 --> 01:11:23,580
You two are definitely sisters.

693
01:11:24,280 --> 01:11:25,350
You even have the same taste in food.

694
01:11:43,970 --> 01:11:45,430
When I was pregnant with Geum Bi,

695
01:11:45,430 --> 01:11:47,470
I was craving these cold noodles.

696
01:11:49,740 --> 01:11:52,940
That's why I went to the cafe that day,
just on the off chance.

697
01:12:00,220 --> 01:12:01,920
And I wanted to see you, too.

698
01:12:09,620 --> 01:12:11,330
I really enjoyed the meal that day.

699
01:12:16,200 --> 01:12:17,400
You said if mine were too spicy,

700
01:12:19,100 --> 01:12:20,700
you'd let me have your cold noodles.

701
01:13:10,650 --> 01:13:13,720
(Geumnyeong-ro 42-gil 17)

702
01:15:15,340 --> 01:15:16,340
I love you.

703
01:15:25,790 --> 01:15:26,790
I love you.

704
01:15:35,960 --> 01:15:39,500
(Thank you for watching
and supporting "Doctor Shin.")

705
01:15:44,440 --> 01:15:47,280
(Doctor Shin)
